Definition: marked by or showing unaffected simplicity and lack of guile or worldly experience
Example: a teenager's naive ignorance of life; the naive assumption that things can only get better; this naive simple creature with wide friendly eyes so eager to believe appearances
Synonyms: noun, attribute, naiveness, SOPHISTICATED, naif, CREDULOUS, UNINFORMED, UNWORLDLY, marked, by, or, showing, unaffected, simplicity, and, lack, of, guile, worldly, experience, a, teenager, s, naive, ignorance, life, the, assumption, that, things, can, only, get, better, this, simple, creature, with, wide, friendly, eyes, so, eager, to, believe, appearances
Category: adj.all
